ANGULAR + STRAPI PROJECT SETUP (FRESH SYSTEM / REINSTALL)

Project Name: employee-customer-ui

---

1. REQUIRED SOFTWARE

---

Install Node.js (recommended LTS version)

Check versions:

node -v
npm -v

Install Angular CLI globally:

npm install -g @angular/cli

Check Angular version:

ng version

---

2. OPEN PROJECT

---

Open terminal and go to project folder:

cd employee-customer-ui

---

3. INSTALL PROJECT DEPENDENCIES

---

npm install

---

4. IF POWERSHELL BLOCKS ANGULAR COMMANDS

---

Run:

Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope Process -ExecutionPolicy Bypass

---

5. START ANGULAR APPLICATION

---

ng serve --open

If port already in use:

ng serve --open --port 4201

---

6. START STRAPI BACKEND

---

Open another terminal

Go to Strapi backend project folder:

cd your-strapi-project

Install packages:

npm install

Start Strapi:

npm run develop

---

7. VERIFY APPLICATION URLS

---

Angular Frontend:

http://localhost:4200

Strapi Backend:

http://localhost:1337

API Test:

http://localhost:1337/api/employees

http://localhost:1337/api/customers

---

8. IF PROJECT FAILS AFTER COPYING TO NEW SYSTEM

---

Delete existing packages:

rm -r node_modules

Delete lock file:

del package-lock.json

Clean npm cache:

npm cache clean --force

Reinstall packages:

npm install

Run application again:

ng serve --open

---

9. INSTALL ANGULAR MATERIAL (IF REQUIRED)

---

npm install @angular/material@16 @angular/cdk@16 @angular/animations@16

Install sass support:

npm install --save-dev sass

---

10. GENERATE COMPONENTS (IF NEEDED)

---

ng generate component components/employee-list
ng generate component components/employee-form
ng generate component components/customer-list
ng generate component components/customer-form

---

11. GENERATE SERVICES (IF NEEDED)

---

ng generate service services/employee
ng generate service services/customer

---

12. REQUIRED MODULES IN app.module.ts

---

Import required modules:

HttpClientModule
FormsModule
BrowserAnimationsModule

---

13. DEFAULT ROUTING EXAMPLE

---

{ path: '', redirectTo: '/employees', pathMatch: 'full' }

---

14. STRAPI POST REQUEST FORMAT

---

Strapi requires POST data in this format:

{
data: object
}

Example Angular API call:

this.http.post(url, {
data: employee
})

---

15. RUN BOTH SERVERS

---

Angular frontend must run:

localhost:4200

AND

Strapi backend must run:

localhost:1337

Both must be running for API calls to work.

---

16. IF ANGULAR COMMAND NOT FOUND

---

Install Angular CLI globally again:

npm install -g @angular/cli

---

17. IF PORT CONFLICT OCCURS

---

Check running process:

netstat -ano | findstr :4200

Run Angular on different port:

ng serve --port 4201
